data.body:
On a stereo setup, `SoundEffectInstance.PlatformSetPan` is sending a bad routing matrix to XAudio:

``` csharp
// https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/develop/MonoGame.Framework/Audio/SoundEffectInstance.XAudio.cs#L147
// Default to full volume for all channels/destinations   
for (var i = 0; i < _panMatrix.Length; i++)
    _panMatrix[i] = 1.0f;
```

``` csharp
// https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/develop/MonoGame.Framework/Audio/SoundEffectInstance.XAudio.cs#L183
case Speakers.Stereo:
case Speakers.TwoPointOne:
case Speakers.Surround:
    _panMatrix[0] = lVal;
    _panMatrix[1] = rVal;
    break;
```

Apparently, on a stereo setup the function would have produced `[lVal, rVal, 1.0f, 1.0f]`, which according to [MSDN](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/microsoft.directx_sdk.ixaudio2voice.ixaudio2voice.setoutputmatrix%28v=vs.85%29.aspx) means the following:
- Send `lVal * left source + rVal * right source` to left output.
- Send `1.0f * left source + 1.0f * right source` to right output.

... which causes clipping and distortion, and failure of panning. Other speaker setups are likely in a similar situation, and should be inspected as well.

Steps to reproduce:
- add the following code to Update
- wiggle your mouse around and notice the logs getting printed
- click the left mouse button and do the same wiggle and notice that their will be no logs until the mouse button is lifted

```
_previousMouseState = _currentMouseState;
_currentMouseState = Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Input.Mouse.GetState();

if( _previousMouseState.X != _currentMouseState.X )
    Debug.WriteLine( "past: {0}, curr: {1}", _previousMouseState.X, _currentMouseState.X );
```
